<TITLE> Channel 1 chairman Selim sued again </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Bagerhat, June 2 (bdnews24.com)  A party activist Friday night sued former BNP lawmaker and Channel 1 chairman MAH Selim for allegedly forcing him to sell a piece of land at a lower price. Mina Rakibul Hasan, better known as Milon Mina, in the case filed with Bagerhat Police Station alleged the former Bagerhat-2 lawmaker had coerced him into selling his 1.17 acres of land in Goalmath village at Tk 2.8 lakh. Mina, a local BNP leader, said Selim had bought the land to set up a college named after his mother. He also alleged that the former MP threatened to frame him in a case if he had not agreed. Bagerhat Sadar police chief Sirajul Islam Chowdhury confirmed the case. Selim, now in jail on charge of corruption, is also facing a lawsuit for extortion. Transport owner Abdul Wadud filed the case Thursday. bdnews2
